'''Roberto Júnior Fernández Torres''' (born 29 March 1988), better known as '''Gatito Fernández''', is a Paraguayan professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for [[Paraguayan Primera División]] club [[Cerro Porteño]] and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].

He is known as ''Gatito'' ({{langx|en|little cat or kitten }}) for being the son of former Paraguayan 1986 World Cup goalkeeper [[Roberto Fernández (footballer, born 1954)|Roberto Fernández]], nicknamed ''Gato'' ({{langx|en|cat}}). Because of his father, who was a goalkeeper at Brazilian clubs, such as [[Sport Club Internacional|Internacional]] and [[Sociedade Esportiva Palmeiras|Palmeiras]], Gatito had lived in Brazil before his professional days.<ref>[https://esporte.uol.com.br/futebol/ultimas-noticias/2019/06/26/inquieto-gatito-dava-problema-na-escola-e-morou-no-rs-por-causa-do-pai.htm Inquieto, Gatito dava problema na escola e morou no RS por causa do pai]</ref>

==Club career==
===Early career===
Fernández started his professional career with [[Paraguayan Primera División]] club [[Cerro Porteño]] in 2007. He became Paraguayan champion with the club in the 2009 Apertura. Following the achievement, he joined [[Argentine Primera División]] side [[Estudiantes de La Plata]]. After a season in the club without any first team appearance, he joined [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Llegó el arquero Fernández a Racing|newspaper=ESPN Deportes|date=16 July 2010|url=https://espndeportes.espn.com/news/story?id=1061582&s=arg&type=story|language=es|access-date=16 July 2010 }}</ref>

In August 2011, [[FC Utrecht]] announced the signing of Fernández on loan for one year to cover a possible departure of [[Michel Vorm]].
<ref>[http://www.vi.nl/Nieuws-item/204468/FC-Utrecht-rondt-komst-van-doelman-Fernandez-af.htm FC Utrecht rondt komst van doelman Fernández af] - Voetbal International {{in lang|nl}}</ref>

===Botafogo===
On 26 November 2016, Fernandéz signed with [[Botafogo de Futebol e Regatas|Botafogo]] on a two-year contract until December 2018, moving on a free transfer.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gatito Fernández assina por dois anos e acerta com o Botafogo até 2018 |url=http://globoesporte.globo.com/rj/futebol/noticia/2016/11/gatito-fernandez-assina-por-dois-anos-e-acerta-com-o-botafogo-ate-2018.html |publisher=Globoesporte.com |date=26 November 2016 |access-date=12 November 2019}}</ref>

On 9 April 2018, after good performances in the [[2017 Copa Libertadores]] and [[2018 Campeonato Carioca]], Botafogo extended contract with Fernandéz until December 2021.<ref>{{cite web |title=Um dos heróis do título, Gatito renova com o Botafogo por mais três anos |url=https://globoesporte.globo.com/futebol/times/botafogo/noticia/heroi-do-titulo-gatito-renova-contrato-com-o-botafogo-por-mais-tres-anos.ghtml |publisher=Globoesporte.com |date=9 April 2018 |access-date=12 November 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Botafogo renova com Gatito Fernández até o final de 2021 |url=https://www.espn.com.br/futebol/artigo/_/id/4176226/botafogo-renova-com-gatito-fernandez-ate-o-final-de-2021 |publisher=ESPN.com.br |date=9 April 2018 |access-date=12 November 2019}}</ref>

On 6 October 2022, he became the foreign player with the most appearances for Botafogo, surpassing his teammate [[Joel Carli]] with 188 games.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gatito bate recorde de jogos de um estrangeiro pelo Botafogo |url=https://ge.globo.com/futebol/times/botafogo/noticia/2022/10/06/gatito-bate-recorde-de-jogos-de-um-estrangeiro-pelo-botafogo.ghtml |publisher=Globoesporte.com |date=6 October 2022 |access-date=25 November 2022}}</ref>

On 2 February 2023, Fernández signed a contract renewal until the end of 2024 with Botafogo.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Redação |date=2 February 2023 |title=Botafogo anuncia renovação de Gatito Fernández; novo contrato vale até 2024 |url=https://fogonarede.com.br/botafogo-anuncia-renovacao-de-gatito-fernandez-novo-contrato-vale-ate-2024/ |access-date=6 April 2024 |website=Fogo na Rede |language=pt-br}}</ref>

On 19 July, Fernández returned to play for Botafogo in a 1–1 draw against the Argentine team Patronato, a game valid for the Copa Sudamericana.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 July 2023 |title=Gatito comemora 'estreia' pelo Botafogo contra Patronato: 'Estava ansioso para o jogo' |url=https://fogonarede.com.br/gatito-comemora-estreia-pelo-botafogo-contra-patronato-estava-ansioso-para-o-jogo/ |access-date=6 April 2024 |website=Fogo na Rede |language=pt-br}}</ref> The game marked ''Gatito'''s return after eight months without playing. Although the goalkeeper had been fully recovered for months from the injury suffered in a game against Atlético Minero at the end of the previous year, his return to the field took a while to happen due to the good performances of his teammate [[Lucas Perri]], who ended up taking over as the starting goalkeeper for Botafogo.

At the end of the season his contract was not renewed, so during his time at the Rio de Janeiro club, he played 222 matches, becoming the fifth goalkeeper with the most games in Botafogo's history.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2024-12-25 |title=Cerro Porteño anuncia contratação de Gatito Fernandez e surpreende torcedores do Botafogo – Jovem Pan |url=https://jovempan.com.br/esportes/futebol/cerro-porteno-anuncia-contratacao-de-gatito-fernandez-e-surpreende-torcedores-do-botafogo.html |access-date=2026-04-30 |website=Cerro Porteño anuncia contratação de Gatito Fernandez e surpreende torcedores do Botafogo – Jovem Pan |language=pt-BR}}</ref>

==International career==
Fernández debuted with the [[Paraguay national under-20 football team|Paraguay U20 national team]] in the [[2007 South American Youth Championship]] replacing the injured [[Blas Hermosilla]]. He was selected for the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay senior squad]] for the [[2011 Copa América]], remaining an unused substitute as the team finished the tournament as the runner-up.

